## Already-recorded constraints (do NOT re-flag these)
- ADR-0001-C1 (ADR-0001): Showcase routing must survive the GitHub Pages sub-path
- ADR-0001-C2 (ADR-0001): Showcase must be mobile-first / responsive
- ADR-0001-C3 (ADR-0001): Homepage presents as a slide deck on all viewports
- ADR-0003-C1 (ADR-0003): Model verdicts via typed structured outputs only
- ADR-0004-C1 (ADR-0004): CI/CD config must not embed secrets
- ADR-0004-C2 (ADR-0004): Pages deploys from the main repo via official actions
- ADR-0004-C3 (ADR-0004): Releases stay GitHub-only (no npm publish)
- ADR-0005-C1 (ADR-0005): Significant UI elements carry stable, descriptive ids
- ADR-0006-C1 (ADR-0006): radar core stays platform-agnostic (no git/host/VCS calls in src/core/)
- ADR-0006-C2 (ADR-0006): radar config comes only from the environment (no .env / file / runtime preconditions)
- ADR-0007-C1 (ADR-0007): core LLM access goes through the ModelClient port, not a concrete provider SDK
- ADR-0008-C1 (ADR-0008): package stays ESM-only (no CommonJS idioms in src/)
- ADR-0008-C2 (ADR-0008): npm publish is gated by publint + attw
- ADR-0009-C1 (ADR-0009): the agent lives at the edge — the pure core stays SDK-free and platform-free
- ADR-0009-C2 (ADR-0009): capture drafts for human review — it never produces accepted intent unattended
- ADR-0010-C1 (ADR-0010): every LLM operation runs through the one shared agent engine, not a bespoke model call or the retired port
- ADR-0010-C2 (ADR-0010): scope-first retrieval stays deterministic — the agent judges, it does not pick which constraints apply

